02/06/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The leader of the main opposition party VMRO-DPMNE, Nikola Gruevski, called for early parliamentary elections during Tuesday's (1 June) parliamentary debate on Prime Minister-designate Hari Kostov's proposed new government. Gruevski also called for a completely new cabinet.
In other news Tuesday, it was reported that the international rating agency Standard & Poor's would assign a credit rating to Macedonia within two months. The rating, in turn, is expected to attract more foreign investment. (Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 02/06/04; Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 01/06/04)
